title: Lorraine Kelly blasts “rubbish” Fifty Shades Darker: “Fifty shades of nonsense”
text:
Lorraine Kelly isn’t one to mince her words – and this morning she let viewers know EXACTLY what she thinks about Fifty Shades Darker. 
When discussing what Jamie Dornan and his wife Amelia Warner wore to the BAFTAs last night, Lorraine gushed about how handsome the Irish actor is. 
“Now that’s a good looking fella and a beautiful woman too,” she said. 
Despite her kind words about Jamie, she had nothing good to say about his film. Lorraine Kelly slated Fifty Shades Darker (Photo: Rex Features) Lorraine praised handsome Jamie Dornan and his wife Amelia Warner (Photo: Getty Images Europe) 
“But that movie’s rubbish,” she added. 
“Fifty shades of nonsense. But he knows it’s rubbish as well.” 
Lorraine was also being open about her views last week when she said she hopes Kylie Minogue finds a man “worthy of her” in the future. 
The television presenter spoke about Kylie’s engagement breakdown on Lorraine, calling it a “terrible shame” that her romance with fiancé Joshua Sasse hadn’t worked out. Lorraine dubbed Fifty Shades 'nonsense' (Photo: PA) Lorraine isn't one to mince her words (Photo: Rex Features) 
“I really hope one day that she finds someone worthy of her,” said Lorraine. 
“Terrible, shame.” 
After calling Joshua "crazy" to let Kylie go, Lorraine then added: “It’s better that she found out now than later.” Lorraine hopes Kylie finds a good man (Photo: ITV) Kylie with now ex Joshua (Photo: Getty Images Europe) Read More Actress linked to Kylie Minogue's ex-fiance 'very upset' over claims she played a part in split 
Meanwhile, Lorraine also backed Ms Minogue in her trademark battle with reality star Kylie Jenner, who wants to trademark the name Kylie. 
"There's only one Kylie!" insisted Lorraine, saying it was a "no" from her to Kylie Jenner being more well known than Kylie Minogue. 
Jenner's trademark claim was rejected in the US last week after Minogue launched a legal battle, but Jenner has appealed against the decision. 
Meanwhile, Kylie, 48, had been planning on scaling back her work commitments to focus on settling down with British actor Joshua, 28. 
But following their split, Kylie is reported to be planning to make a big musical comeback by recording her 14th studio album. Kylie Minogue (Photo: Getty) 
Kylie has just signed a new deal with BMG and plans to pour her heartbreak into her music. 
"So happy to announce my new record label is BMG," she wrote on Instagram. "I promise you will have my heart and soul in this next record." 
Earlier this month, Kylie spoke out for the first time since throwing him out of the house they shared. (Photo: FameFlynet.uk.com) 
In an emotional statement posted on her Instagram page, pop queen thanked her fans for all their support and confirmed she and Josh have broken up. 
"Thank you for all your love and support throughout this recent chapter of my life," she said. 
"Thank you now for your love and understanding with the news that Josh and I have decided to go our separate ways. We wish only the best for each other as we venture towards new horizons. #thesunalwaysrises ." 
It came as rumours about Joshua's friendship with another woman started to swirl. 
The devastated Kylie is said to have kicked the Brit actor out of their West London home. Read More
